## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Leaflet.js + React Leaflet (GIS map)
- Recharts (dashboard charts)
- React Router v6
- Axios

### Backend
- Node.js + Express.js
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- JWT Authentication (jsonwebtoken)
- bcryptjs (password hashing)

---

## Features

### Authentication & Authorization
- JWT-based authentication with 24-hour token expiry
- Role-based access control — Admin, Scheduler, Viewer
- Protected routes on both frontend and backend
- bcrypt password hashing

### Bus Management
- Add, edit, delete buses
- Filter by status (active / maintenance / inactive)
- Search by bus number
- Export to CSV
- Stat cards showing fleet breakdown

### Driver Management
- Add, edit, delete drivers
- Shift time management (shiftStart / shiftEnd)
- Driver status tracking (available / on-duty / on-rest / off-duty)
- Rest period display — shows restUntil time
- Search by name or license number

### Linked Duty Scheduling
- Assign a specific driver to a specific bus for their entire shift
- System enforces driver stays with same bus — blocks reassignment to different bus
- Backend conflict detection prevents double-booking

### Unlinked Duty Scheduling
- Driver completes a trip and hands over bus to another driver
- Configurable rest duration per schedule (default 30 minutes)
- System automatically sets driver to on-rest after completion
- Driver blocked from new schedules during rest period
- restUntil timestamp stored on driver document

### Conflict Detection
- Bus conflict — same bus cannot be assigned at same departure time
- Driver conflict — same driver cannot be assigned at same departure time
- Linked duty conflict — driver cannot be linked to two different buses simultaneously
- Rest period conflict — driver on rest cannot be assigned new schedule
- All conflicts return clear error messages from backend

### Route Management
- Add routes with real coordinates from Google Maps
- Coordinates auto-parsed from pasted lat,lng values
- Live route preview on map while adding stops
- Delete routes

### GIS Map Visualization
- Leaflet.js interactive map centered on Delhi
- All routes drawn as colored polylines
- Overlapping routes highlighted in red dashed lines
- Stop markers with popup showing stop name and route
- Click route on map or sidebar to highlight it
- Route selection shows blue glow effect
- Overlap detection based on shared stop names

### Dashboard
- Real-time stat cards — buses, drivers, routes, schedules
- Schedule status bar chart (Recharts)
- Fleet status breakdown with progress bars
- Driver status breakdown
- Recent schedules table
- Quick stats — linked/unlinked/completed/cancelled counts

### Role-Based UI
- Admin — full access, all buttons visible
- Scheduler — can create/manage, no delete buttons
- Viewer — read only, Actions column hidden entirely, no add/edit/delete
- Export CSV available to all roles

